(secondQuint)Posterior Cruciate Retaining (PCR) Versus Posterior Cruciate Substituting (PCS) Total Knee Arthroplasty (TKA).

 RCT of 100 subjects undergoing primary TKA who were randomized to received either a SCORPIO cent PCS or PCR TKA.

 Subjects were evaluated pre-operatively and at 2 and 10 years post-operatively using the Western Ontario (WOMAC) Osteoarthritis Index, the RAND-36 and knee range of motion (2 years only).

 Complication and revision rates were also evaluated.

